# API layer rules

<!--
TEMPLATE for a SCOPED rule (Cursor .mdc). The orchestrator emits one .mdc per area that needs
path-specific rules, filling globs + body from the system design and conventions.

The point of scoped rules is the TOKEN BUDGET: these load ONLY when a matching file is in
context, so the always-on AGENTS.md stays lean. Keep each .mdc dense and imperative — rules at
the "right altitude": specific enough to guide, not brittle scripts, not vague platitudes.

Frontmatter:
- description : one line; when this rule applies.
- globs       : file patterns that trigger auto-attach.
- alwaysApply : true only for rules that must load every turn (use sparingly — it taxes context).
-->

- Every endpoint maps to an `API-###` in [docs/08-api-spec.md](../docs/08-api-spec.md); add the
  ID in a comment above the handler.
- Validate all input at the boundary; never trust client data. Use the shared validator, not
  ad-hoc checks.
- Return a typed result/error envelope — never throw raw across the API boundary.
- Every new endpoint declares its auth/authz. An unauthenticated public endpoint must carry a
  comment explaining why that is safe.
- Parameterize all queries. No string-built SQL.
- New endpoint ⇒ new test keyed to the `F-###` it serves (see docs/11-qa-test-plan.md).
